Trade/Device Name(s): SAFECARE Urine Test Amphetamine (Cassette, Cup, DipCard)
SAFECARE Urine Test Cocaine (Cassette, Cup, DipCard)
SAFECARE Urine Test Marijuana (Cassette, Cup, DipCard)
Regulation Name(s): Cocaine and Cocaine Metabolite Test System
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for SAFECARE urine tests for qualitative detection of amphetamine, cocaine metabolite, and cannabinoids using immunochromatographic lateral flow assay formats (cassette, cup, dipcard).
Indications for Use Summary: Qualitative detection of amphetamine, benzoylecgonine, and cannabinoids in human urine at specified cutoffs; provides preliminary screening, for prescription and over-the-counter in vitro diagnostic use.
